However, their "Snootiness" and tendency to surrender to germans at the drop of a hat are overwhelming, (if perhaps unfair) stereotypes of the French.<br>
<br>
If someone mentions Canadians, they are often stereotyped as Heavyweight Beer drinkers, who consider Poutine to be a delicacy.<br>
<br>
If Someone mentions England, you immediately get the stereotype of really bad food and dentistry.<br>
<br>
Likewise, if someone mentions the US in another country, you are likely to get a stereotype of a bunch of uncouth yokels with gunracks in our pickup trucks, who consider a Big Mac with a Coke to be a delicacy.<br>
