<br>
I realise that some sections of the US do like to taunt the french with the collapse of 1940. But 'surrender to the Germans at the drop of a hat' IS unfair. VERY unfair.<br>
<br>
Some other statistics that may interest you, from just 25 years earlier... well within living memory of 1940.<br>
<br>
From 1914 to 1918 France mobilised 8,410,000 men. By 1918, 76% of them were casualties of war. 1,357,800 dead, 4,266,000 wounded, 537,000 MIA. A total of 6,160,800.<br>
<br>
Do you have the slightest conception of the national trauma that accompanied that? At all? I can barely understand it. Our casualty rate was half that, 34%, and it was still routinely assumed through to the 1960s that a significant number of women would not find husbands, because there were too few men. Society reeled after the war, and the much reviled appeasement policy was largely driven by determination to avoid it.<br>
<br>
The French were not enthusiastic about the Second World War, that's true. But is it any wonder? after six million casualties, SIX MILLION!<br>
<br>
No offence, Meddik, but while I can appreciate the occasional joke, it might be better if you backed off just a little bit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ullabaktharr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llabak Tharr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 6:23:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4495.topic&index=103>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Axis of Evil&quot;</span><hr size=1> Just for the record casualty |= death.  Any wounding is considered a casualty, and so a 76% casualty rate doesn't mean that 6 Milion men died during the war.<br>
